# Browser-extension signing keys.
# The public key + derived extension id are committed so the unpacked
# extension has a stable identity (.keys/EXTENSION_ID, extension.pub.b64).
# The private key must NEVER be committed — anyone with it can sign a
# malicious CRX that Chrome treats as equivalent to ours.
packages/browser-extension/.keys/*.pem
packages/browser-extension/.keys/*.key
# Canonical location — OUTSIDE the loaded extension dir so Chrome's unpacked
# loader doesn't scan/ship private keys. Whole directory is ignored.
packages/browser-extension-keys/

